.TH "cxgb4_best_mtu" 9 "cxgb4_best_mtu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cxgb4_best_mtu \- find the entry in the MTU table closest to an MTU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" cxgb4_best_mtu
.BI "(const unsigned short *mtus "  ","
.BI "unsigned short mtu "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtus" 12
the HW MTU table
.IP "mtu" 12
the target MTU
.IP "idx" 12
index of selected entry in the MTU table

Returns the index and the value in the HW MTU table that is closest to
but does not exceed \fImtu\fP, unless \fImtu\fP is smaller than any value in the
table, in which case that smallest available value is selected.
